{
  "video_id": "h8f79mUI1ec",
  "title": "What is Persistent Memory Over Fabric? | Intel Software",
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 500.0,
      "end_time": 1830.0,
      "text": "Hi I'm Chet Douglas."
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 1830.0,
      "end_time": 4530.0,
      "text": "In this video, I'll explain\npersistent memory over fabric"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 4530.0,
      "end_time": 8160.0,
      "text": "or PMOF and why it will become\na key technology for cloud"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 8160.0,
      "end_time": 12210.0,
      "text": "and high performance computing."
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 12210.0,
      "end_time": 15330.0,
      "text": "Pure math is largely rooted\nin persistent memory."
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 15330.0,
      "end_time": 18420.0,
      "text": "Persistent memory, sometimes\ncalled storage class memory,"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 18420.0,
      "end_time": 21270.0,
      "text": "is only recently available\non modern hardware."
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 21270.0,
      "end_time": 23340.0,
      "text": "This is due to the emergence\nof new technologies"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 23340.0,
      "end_time": 26430.0,
      "text": "such as Intel's 3D\ncross point memory."
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 26430.0,
      "end_time": 28080.0,
      "text": "In this video, we\nwill discuss how"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 28080.0,
      "end_time": 30750.0,
      "text": "to utilize PMOF to\nmove data in and out"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 30750.0,
      "end_time": 34170.0,
      "text": "of persistent memory attached\nto many physical systems."
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 34170.0,
      "end_time": 36120.0,
      "text": "If you'd like to learn\nthe basics in utilizing"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 36120.0,
      "end_time": 38820.0,
      "text": "persistent memory on a\nsingle physical system"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 38820.0,
      "end_time": 42060.0,
      "text": "and how to move data efficiently\ninto and out of that memory,"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 42060.0,
      "end_time": 44640.0,
      "text": "check out the What is Persistent\nMemory videos provided"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 44640.0,
      "end_time": 45990.0,
      "text": "in the links."
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 45990.0,
      "end_time": 47640.0,
      "text": "Cloud in high\nperformance computing"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 47640.0,
      "end_time": 50070.0,
      "text": "requires data to be moved\nbetween hundreds or even"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 50070.0,
      "end_time": 51990.0,
      "text": "thousands of physical systems."
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 51990.0,
      "end_time": 54960.0,
      "text": "Data may be replicated across\nmultiple nodes for redundancy"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 54960.0,
      "end_time": 56010.0,
      "text": "and protection."
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 56010.0,
      "end_time": 58650.0,
      "text": "Or the data can be split\nacross physical systems"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 58650.0,
      "end_time": 60090.0,
      "text": "for performance."
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 60090.0,
      "end_time": 61800.0,
      "text": "High performance\nnetworking fabrics"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 61800.0,
      "end_time": 65269.0,
      "text": "provide this interconnect\nbetween these physical systems."
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 65269.00000000001,
      "end_time": 67380.0,
      "text": "The fabrics utilize\nnetwork adapter hardware"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 67380.0,
      "end_time": 69900.0,
      "text": "in each physical system\nto move the data using"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 69900.0,
      "end_time": 71610.0,
      "text": "a point to point connection."
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 71610.0,
      "end_time": 73720.0,
      "text": "Two types of fabrics\nare typically used."
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 73720.0,
      "end_time": 75870.0,
      "text": "The first is TCP/IP\nbased networks"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 75870.0,
      "end_time": 78450.0,
      "text": "that utilize the CPU on\neach end of the connection"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 78450.0,
      "end_time": 80140.0,
      "text": "to move the data."
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 80140.0,
      "end_time": 83450.0,
      "text": "The second is remote DMA\ncable networks or RDMA."
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 83450.0,
      "end_time": 87220.0,
      "text": "It is a more efficient transport\nthat will be utilized in PMOF."
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 87220.0,
      "end_time": 90660.0,
      "text": "It utilizes a special network\nadapter hardware or arnix"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 90660.0,
      "end_time": 92820.0,
      "text": "to offload the data\nmovement from the CPU"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 92820.0,
      "end_time": 94830.0,
      "text": "to each system's\nnetwork adapter."
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 94830.0,
      "end_time": 97410.0,
      "text": "This improves system\nperformance by allowing the CPUs"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 97410.0,
      "end_time": 101400.0,
      "text": "to data process and the arnix\nto move data between systems."
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 101400.0,
      "end_time": 103010.0,
      "text": "When moving data\nbetween systems,"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 103010.0,
      "end_time": 105810.0,
      "text": "volatile DRAM memory\nis typically utilized."
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 105810.0,
      "end_time": 107550.0,
      "text": "Once the data is\nwritten into the DRAM"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 107550.0,
      "end_time": 109710.0,
      "text": "on remote physical\nsystem, the system"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 109710.0,
      "end_time": 111750.0,
      "text": "is notified that the\ndata has been moved,"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 111750.0,
      "end_time": 115410.0,
      "text": "and the local CPU can begin\nprocessing the new data."
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 115410.0,
      "end_time": 117360.0,
      "text": "Now with persistent\nmemory over fabric,"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 117360.0,
      "end_time": 119500.0,
      "text": "it is possible to\nreplace the vault of DRAM"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 119500.0,
      "end_time": 121260.0,
      "text": "in the system with\npersistent memory."
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 121260.0,
      "end_time": 124440.0,
      "text": "This allows us to utilize RDMA\nwith persistent memory instead"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 124440.0,
      "end_time": 125940.0,
      "text": "of DRAM."
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 125940.0,
      "end_time": 129449.0,
      "text": "PMOF adheres to the storage\nnetworking industry association"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 129449.00000000001,
      "end_time": 133410.0,
      "text": "or SNIA programming model which\nrequires that any CPU caches be"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 133410.0,
      "end_time": 136830.0,
      "text": "flushed before the persistence\nof the data can be guaranteed."
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 136830.0,
      "end_time": 140040.0,
      "text": "After data is written into the\npersistent memory using RDMA,"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 140040.0,
      "end_time": 142140.0,
      "text": "the software will need\nto flush the node CPU"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 142140.0,
      "end_time": 144270.0,
      "text": "caches before the\nsoftware can assume"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 144270.0,
      "end_time": 145860.0,
      "text": "the data to be persistent."
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 145860.0,
      "end_time": 148770.0,
      "text": "Alternatively, if the\nsystem can bypass CPU caches"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 148770.0,
      "end_time": 152250.0,
      "text": "when moving the data, CPU\nflushes are no longer required."
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 152250.0,
      "end_time": 155400.0,
      "text": "PMOF supplies two solutions\nto accomplish this."
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 155400.0,
      "end_time": 158010.0,
      "text": "The persistent memory\ndevelopment kit or PMDK"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 158010.0,
      "end_time": 160410.0,
      "text": "provides a native\nPMOF solution that"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 160410.0,
      "end_time": 162540.0,
      "text": "supports the standard\nhigh-performance networking"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 162540.0,
      "end_time": 163350.0,
      "text": "protocols."
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 163350.0,
      "end_time": 167130.0,
      "text": "PMDK supports one simple PMOF\nuse case-- persistent memory"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 167130.0,
      "end_time": 170760.0,
      "text": "replication from a local system\nto one or more remote systems."
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 170760.0,
      "end_time": 172920.0,
      "text": "This provides high-performance\ndata redundancy"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 172920.0,
      "end_time": 174840.0,
      "text": "across multiple\nfeathered events."
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 174840.0,
      "end_time": 177210.0,
      "text": "Once your application\nis ported to PMDK,"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 177210.0,
      "end_time": 180030.0,
      "text": "enabling PMOF to replicate\npersistent memory"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 180030.0,
      "end_time": 181740.0,
      "text": "is done with a\nsimple set of updates"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 181740.0,
      "end_time": 185160.0,
      "text": "to existing PMDK\nconfiguration files."
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 185160.0,
      "end_time": 186840.0,
      "text": "No further changes\nto your application"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 186840.0,
      "end_time": 189450.0,
      "text": "are required to make use\nof this powerful feature."
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 189450.0,
      "end_time": 190454.0,
      "text": "Thanks for watching."
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 190454.0,
      "end_time": 192870.0,
      "text": "To learn more, check out the\nPersistent Memory Development"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 192870.0,
      "end_time": 195330.0,
      "text": "Kit playlist and see\nthe links provided."
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 195330.0,
      "end_time": 198000.0,
      "text": "Don't forget to like this video\nand subscribe to the Intel"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 198000.0,
      "end_time": 199690.0,
      "text": "software YouTube channel."
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 199690.0,
      "end_time": 201440.0,
      "text": "Thank you."
    }
  ]
